Several of the attacks took place in the capital city of Colombo.
In Colombo, victims were pouring into the emergency room of the National Hospital of Sri Lanka in all states of physical and psychological trauma.
One couple came to Sri Lanka for their honeymoon, where the wife was killed in the bombing, he said.
Family members of the victims from India, Sri Lanka and the Middle East sat silently in plastic chairs lining a hallway, awkwardly holding the water bottles they had been offered.
